+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014XJST8KHSaSjSL6ntKCYr4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Fj9cyPK85PNyQgpz6yDR2y","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-versioned-document-store-design.md","content":"# Versioned Document Store with Structural Merge - Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nSingle-module in-memory store. All state lives in a `DocumentStore` class instance.\n\n### Data Model\n\n```\nDocumentStore\n  branches: Map<branchName, BranchState>\n  currentBranch: string (default \"main\")\n  branchPoints: Map<branchName, { fromBranch, snapshot }>\n\nBranchState\n  documents: Map<documentId, DocumentRecord>\n\nDocumentRecord\n  content: object (deep-cloned on store/retrieve)\n  versions: Version[] (chronological)\n  deleted: boolean\n\nVersion\n  id: string (uuid-like, using counter for simplicity)\n  timestamp: number\n  content: object (deep-cloned snapshot)\n```\n\n### Branch Points / Common Ancestor\n\nWhen `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` is called:\n- Deep clone the source branch's entire document map as a snapshot\n- Store this snapshot as the \"branch point\" keyed by `(branchName, sourceBranch)` pair\n- On merge, the common ancestor is this snapshot\n\n### Three-Way Merge Algorithm\n\nFor `merge(sourceBranch)` into current branch:\n1. Find the branch point snapshot (common ancestor)\n2. For each document that exists in base, ours, or theirs:\n   - If only one side modified: take that side's changes\n   - If document created only on one side: include it\n   - If document deleted on one side, unchanged on other: delete it\n   - If both sides modified: do field-level recursive diff\n3. Recursive field diff:\n   - Walk all keys at each level\n   - If a field changed only on one side vs base: take that change\n   - If both changed to same value: no conflict\n   - If both changed to different values: conflict\n4. Return MergeResult with merged contents, conflicts, and applied flag\n\n### Deep Cloning\n\nUse `structuredClone()` on all content going in/out of the store.\n\n## File Structure\n\n- `src/index.ts` - All exports: DocumentStore class, interfaces\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- CRUD operations: create, get, update, delete, error cases\n- Version history: getHistory, getVersion\n- Branching: create, switch, isolation\n- Merging: clean merge, conflicts, field-level merge, document-level changes\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":270,"cache_read_input_tokens":24650,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":270},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e1d01d48-a1d5-4f9a-aad6-9550ae28dcd7","uuid":"c5a3390f-b76c-4081-87c5-189fb1080ef7"}
